try{}                - must be followed by either catch or finally block.
catch(Exception e){} - Exceptions thrown in the try block are caught here.
finally              - cleanup codes are written here,Ex: DB connection can be closed after usage.
throw                - Used to throw an exception, must be caught by a catch block.
throws               - Written in method signature, says this method might throw an exception.
try-with-resources   - It doesn't need a catch or finally block as it implements AutoCloseable.
Throwable            - Throwable is the super class for both Error and Exception.
Chained Exception    - Chained Exceptions are used to find the cause of the Exception. Ex: throw new Exception(new NullPointerException());



